    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in UE security capability encoding\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_ue_security_capability()` function in the NAS security handling contained a buffer length validation error that could cause memory corruption when encoding security capabilities with GPRS support. The issue occurred when the function was called with a buffer smaller than the actual encoded length.\n\nThe bug was caused by an incorrect minimum length definition that only accounted for the value portion rather than the total encoded length including the length field. This led to the function accepting buffers that were too small, causing writes beyond allocated memory.\n\nUnder certain network conditions where UEs reported GPRS-only security support, this could lead to memory corruption in the NAS message buffer.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/UeSecurityCapability.h`: Updated `UE_SECURITY_CAPABILITY_MINIMUM_LENGTH` from 2 to 3 to reflect correct minimum total encoded length\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/UeSecurityCapability.c`: Removed redundant bitwise OR operations with 0x00 for cleaner code\n\n"
}